The paper proposes a novel approach for Machine Reading Comprehension (MRC) with multiple-choice questions, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the proposed model involves attention mechanisms and convolutional operations, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks, as it involves reading passages and selecting answers from multiple choices.
